<br>
Given:<br>
<br>
Crazy people do crazy things.<br>
Crazy person doing horrible crimeX &lt; sane person doing horrible crimeX.  (from a &quot;is this scary?&quot; Point of View... I.e. the mumbling, shambling mound of walking rags takes an uzi from his cart and sprays a crowd.  Sure its horrible.  People died.  But its far less scary, less &quot;i-could-be-next&quot; than an investment banker, a crossing guard, a maid, or some other Random_Joe doing it)<br>
<br>
If you accept the above statements as true, then Dubya could quite possibly be the dangerous man on earth.  Sure there are other folks out there who are strickly more dangerous, but they all also seem to fit into one of the &quot;whackjob&quot; catagories.  Dubya does most of every thing he does out of ignorance, pigheadedness, or blindly doing what his puppetmasters/handelers tell him too (and hell, as we've seen from the way he speaks, compared to the actual quecards he gets, he can't even get that correct).<br>
<br>
