<br>
But I was neglected as a child due to socioeconomic circumstances beyond my own control, and was never given ample opportunity to be taught shoe tying. This caused me great emotional trauma as I progressed through middle and high school wearing sandals slippers and velcro closures. In gym class the teacher would have to retie my sneakers much to my great chagrin. The ineveitable ridicule involved in athletics was the deciding factor in my inability to connect to my peers and a contributor to my spiraling descent into a sordid life of drug abuse and violent behavior.  <br>
<br>
I am so extermely phobic of shoelaces at this point that I experience panic attacks whenever I see a Nike commercial. Surely you see my need for financial assistance. I cannot possibly concentrate on working and paying my bills while I am so severly debilitated by this horrid twist of fate. Perhaps after years of treatment I will be once again a productive member of society, but until that time I think it is clear that I will require the full support of our governments resources to overcome this malady without the daily pressure of modern life and its many responsibilities.<br>
<br>
